snippet.textDisplay: Just finished listening to the whole album, and I can't see an album topping it this year – even someone with stature of Kendrick Lamar with his reputation for hardly missing with albums, would have to drop something HARD to top this. Lot of replay value and a very cohesive work despite range of genres—elements of afrobeat in "Play Play (feat. Burna Boy)," , dancehall in "Repeat (feat. Koffee)," and drill "No Denying" all displayed—weaved in and throughout the hip-hop-heavy sound that takes up most of the album. Common Sense may have more hits and range, but Big Conspiracy is a consistent, focused body of work, no doubt.
